<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-651-977  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 651 977.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  June 5 1989 v6 n22 p11(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Voice mail service bureaus offer host of advantages: Tigon, GTETeleMessager top list of providers. (evaluation of servicesoffered )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Herbst, Kris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A key choice in considering voice mail is whether to subscribe toan outside service bureau or buy an in-house system.andP;  Servicebureau users do not need to make a large investment in newhardware.andP;  Service bureaus are ideal for companies with widelytraveled sales forces or geographically dispersed sales.andP;  Two ofthe leading voice mail services, Tigon Corp and GTE TeleMessager,are similar in many respects because their equipment support comesfrom VMX Inc. Both nationwide services offer 24-hour customerservice hot lines, the capability to send a single message tomultiple recipients, and management reports that track usage bydepartment, individual and type of access.andP;  Tigon emphasizes itsinternational reach while GTE TeleMessager stresses its IntegratedVoice Response devices, which enable users to interact with thevoice mail system by using their telephone keypad.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tigon Corp. (services)GTE TeleMessager (services)VMX Inc. (products).andO;Topic:     Voice MailService BureausCost Benefit AnalysisCommunications Service SuppliersSystem Selection.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>